## Replace CloudFetch params-only check with real runtime probe

Context: The CloudFetch readiness check was bailing out early with
"CloudFetch disabled by SQL connection params (use_cloud_fetch=False)"
whenever ``get_sql_connection_params`` had ``use_cloud_fetch=False``,
hiding whether CloudFetch could actually work at runtime. The previous
runtime "capability check" was a static network reachability probe on a
hard-coded storage host pattern (``*.storage.cloud.databricks.com``),
which did not reflect actual workspace egress behaviour and skipped
non-AWS workspaces.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/databricks/DatabricksAuth.py
   - Added ``probe_cloud_fetch_capability()`` that actually issues a
     bounded ``SELECT 1`` with ``use_cloud_fetch=True`` and caches the
     ``(capable, reason)`` outcome at the class level for ~5 minutes.
   - Added ``cloud_fetch_status(force=False)`` for diagnostic callers
     that want both the verdict and the reason.
   - ``can_use_cloud_fetch()`` now reads cached probe outcome (or env
     overrides), defaulting conservatively (False in Apps mode, True
     locally) without triggering side-effecting probes from
     ``get_sql_connection_params``.
   - Replaced socket-reachability probe (``getaddrinfo`` + TCP/443 to a
     derived ``*.storage.cloud.databricks.com`` host) with the real SQL
     probe path.
2. src/shared/fastapi/health.py
   - ``_check_cloud_fetch`` now always calls
     ``DatabricksAuth.probe_cloud_fetch_capability()`` and surfaces the
     real ``(status, reason)``, so ``/health`` reports the actual probe
     outcome instead of the connection-param flag.
3. tests/conftest.py
   - Set ``DATABRICKS_DISABLE_CLOUD_FETCH=1`` and unset
     ``DATABRICKS_FORCE_CLOUD_FETCH`` in the autouse env so SQL probes
     in tests do not perform live ``databricks.sql.connect`` calls with
     ``use_cloud_fetch=True`` against the unreachable test host.
4. tests/test_auth.py
   - Updated CloudFetch capability tests to cover the new SQL-probe
     path (success/failure), env override behaviour
     (``DATABRICKS_FORCE_CLOUD_FETCH`` /
     ``DATABRICKS_DISABLE_CLOUD_FETCH``), Apps-mode conservative
     default, and the missing-pyarrow prerequisite path.
   - Extended ``_clear_databricks_env`` to clear the new CloudFetch env
     overrides for isolated tests.
5. tests/test_health.py
   - Restored simple readiness shape assertions; the new conftest env
     ensures probes run quickly.

