## Reduce KG search hangs in deployed app

Context: Knowledge Graph search on deployed Apps could run for several minutes
with the UI stuck on "Searching..." when preview expansion scanned too many
subjects. We need bounded server work and a deterministic client timeout.

Changes:

1. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   Preview phase now requests at most `max_preview + 1` seed subjects from the
   graph backend so the API can detect capping without unbounded scans.
2. src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreBackend.py
   Extended `find_seed_subjects` with optional `limit` parameter.
3. src/back/core/graphdb/ladybugdb/LadybugFlatStore.py
   Implemented `limit` in Cypher queries and optimized the
   `(entity_type + value)` path to search first, then type-filter the matched
   subset (avoids materializing huge typed-subject sets).
4. src/front/static/query/js/query-sigmagraph.js
   Added `_fetchWithTimeout` with abort support and applied timeouts to KG
   preview and expand requests, so users get a clear timeout message instead of
   an indefinite spinner.

