## Mitigate deployed KG expansion 502 errors

Context: Users still hit `Graph expansion failed (502)` in deployed Apps after
search, which indicates the expansion workload can exceed gateway/runtime limits
for large neighborhoods.

Changes:

1. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   Tightened expansion budget for Databricks Apps:
   - depth capped to 3 in app mode;
   - max entities capped to 3000 in app mode;
   - triple fetch now runs in batches (250 subjects per batch in app mode)
     instead of a single large query;
   - added a fetch time budget (40s in app mode) that returns capped partial
     results rather than letting the request run until gateway failure.
2. src/front/static/query/js/query-sigmagraph.js
   Improved 502 handling for expansion requests with a specific actionable
   message telling users to reduce Depth/Max entities and retry.

