## Right-click "Expand neighbours" on graph nodes

Context: Users want to enrich the displayed knowledge graph by expanding a
selected entity in place rather than re-running a full SPARQL query. Adding a
right-click action that pulls the induced N-hop subgraph from the backend and
merges it into the existing visualisation. Default depth is 2 hops so a single
click reveals not just direct neighbours but also their immediate connections,
which is what users typically want when exploring a node.

Changes:

1. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   New `GET /dtwin/neighbors` endpoint. BFS-expands a seed URI by `depth`
   hops (default 2, max 5) using the existing `expand_entity_neighbors` /
   `get_triples_for_subjects` triplestore primitives, and returns the
   induced subgraph triples (objects pointing outside the visited set are
   filtered out so the front-end never renders dangling edges).
2. src/front/static/query/js/query-sigmagraph.js
   - Added "Expand neighbours (2 hops)" entry to the node right-click menu
     (hidden for super-/cluster nodes); wired the dispatcher so it calls
     the new `SigmaGraph.expandHop(seedUri)` method.
   - `SigmaGraph.expandHop()` fetches the new endpoint, de-duplicates rows
     against `lastQueryResults`, rebuilds `d3NodesData`/`d3LinksData` via
     `buildGraph`, refreshes the Sigma view, highlights newly-added nodes
     for 6s, and frames the camera around them.
3. tests/test_routes.py
   Added smoke tests for the new endpoint covering the missing-URI and
   no-domain paths.

